@ENDNODE
@NODE "FKT-ABS"
@TITLE "abs()"
@NEXT "FKT-ACOS"
@TOC "Functions"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual ----------------------------------------------------- abs() -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "Functions" "abs()"
@{U}abs()@{UU}

@{B}sypnosis:@{UB}
   @{B}abs(@{I}x @{UI})@{UB}

@{B}arguments:@{UB}
   @{I}x @{UI}: number, vector

@{B}result:@{UB}
   number

   If @{I}x @{UI}  is a  number, the  absolute of @{I}x  @{UI} is  returned. For  a real number
@{I}abs(x) @{UI} is @{I}x @{UI}, if @{I}x >=0 @{UI} and @{I}-x @{UI}, if @{I}x < 0 @{UI}. The absolute of a complex number
is @{I}abs(x) = sqrt(re x ^ 2 + im x ^ 2) @{UI}.

   If @{I}x @{UI} is a vector, the (euclidian) length of the vector

                   @{I}abs(x) = sqrt(sum  x_i), i = 1...dim  x @{UI}

   is returned.


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ę by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
@ENDNODE
