@NODE "FKT-ARC"
@TITLE "arc()"
@NEXT "FKT-ARCCOS"
@PREV "FKT-ACOT"
@TOC "Functions"
@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}- Laplace Manual ----------------------------------------------------- arc() -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}

@REM KEY 0 0 "Functions" "arc()"
@{U}arc()@{UU}

@{B}sypnosis:@{UB}
   @{B}arc(@{I}x @{UI})@{UB}

@{B}arguments:@{UB}
   @{I}x @{UI}: number

@{B}result:@{UB}
   number

   If @{I}x @{UI} is a complex number, the angle between @{I}x @{UI} and the x-axis in the gaus-
sian plane will be returned, which is defined as

                         @{I}arc x = arctan im x / re x @{UI}

   The @{I}arc () @{UI} of an positive real number  is defined as @{I}1 @{UI} and of a negative
as @{I}-1 @{UI}.


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ę by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
