@{B}arguments:@{UB}
   @{I}handle @{UI}: plotter handle
   @{I}f @{UI}: any expression
   @{I}x, t @{UI}: identifier

@{B}result:@{UB}
   number

   Add the function @{I}f @{UI} to the plotter referenced  by @{I}handle @{UI}, using @{I}x @{UI} and @{I}t @{UI}
(if supplied) as  variables. If  @{I}handle @{UI} refers  to an  animated plotter,  you
should supply @{I}t @{UI}; otherwise the function cannot be animated. For not  animated
plotters, supplying @{I}t @{UI} is useless and usually results in a not plotable func-
tion.

   @{I}plot_addfunc  @{UI} returns the index of the inserted function (1 for the first
function, 2 for the second, etc.).


@{FG SHINE}@{BG SHADOW}@{B}------------------------------------------------------------------ ę by P!\K -@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}@{UB}
